’Ł@a8827134c237fc84da0f2dcbcf4e2e3eb16fac12f8b694f740c49a9a45ab0817Ł»Title: title: exec
Path: Examples
Content:
Execute external 'ps aux' tool
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> exec ps aux


```
Execute 'nautilus'
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> exec nautilus


```
’Ł@004fc5890523a08387e1256299f20874d6dfdd219c572fd21c7f31e7978eaf04ŁäTitle: title: exec
Path: Notes
Content:
On Unix-based systems, the current process is replaced with the command.

On Windows based systems, Nushell will wait for the command to finish and then exit with the command's exit code.
